snippet.textDisplay:
The "Ø" is pronounced almost exactly like the "ea" in early.


The R in most Norwegian words are way more pronounced than in english. Couldn't really find any good equivalents.. But try making an over the top Russian accent and try saying "early". The "r" sound there is pretty close to how we pronounce "r"


S - Normal S, Like "s" in "sand"
Ø - ea(rly)
R - Russian "r"
F - Normal F, like the "f" in "Feather)
U - like the "U" in "Bullet"
GL - Continue with the "l" sound from Bullet for these two
Ø - again, ea(rly)
YA - Try saying Arya's name from Game of Thrones, just drop the "Ar" and you have the "YA" sound left


Kind of messy.. I have no idea how to explain it using the phonetic alphabet, but it is hopefully easy to follow..


This literally translates to "South (SØR) Bird (FUGL) Island (ØYA)


And to the no Norwegain travel video having norwegian people speaking Norwegian..


We are a people that is ridiculously proud of everything that is Norwegian. But we are also pretty much literally the most shy and introvert people on the planet. So we usually don't make that big of a deal around our language, and focus instead on our culture, art, music and most of all, our nature. That's why most videos will have some kind of Norwegian music accompanying pictures of things that we are proud of.


Oh, and keep up the good work! I have been an eager theorist for several years now, trying to spread your theories to the rest of Norway.

snippet.textDisplay: I will explain as I have watched the movie over 5 times, the reason Elsa froze was because of the song from the beginning, it was called All is Found. In the middle of the song it says go to far and you'll be drowned, which refers to the area Elsa fell into. If you listen carefully, the song plays as Elsa goes farther down into the river. When Elsa freezes in the river, it technically is the same as drowning. So that's why she freezes in Ahtohallan. I recommend watching the movie again, and please look for the finer details. It really helps with the storyline if you didn't already understand.
